3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper uses graph theory, which is closely related to computational geometry. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses polynomial-time data reduction, which is a fundamental concept in data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper studies the parameterization of graph coloring problems, which is a topic that has connections to game theory.
